dct_title_s: Rutlandshire, with Oukham and Stanford, her bordering neighbour newely described
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Insets: Oukham.--Stanford. Shows hundred boundaries and main roads. From: The theatre of the empire of Great Britaine ... / divided and described by Iohn Speed. London : And are to be solde by I. Sudbury and G. Humble, 1611. On verso of map: Rutland-shire. Book I, Chap 30; p. 59-60; signature Ll.
dct_publisher_sm: [London], Solde by M. John Sudbury and George Humbell, in Popes head alley against the Exchange, [1610]
